    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-04-04T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-04-04T03:00:00-05:00" n="22"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">895B.13/4–450: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-04-04T18:00:00+10:00"
                            >April 4, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>453. Redeptel 320, April 3.<note n="1" xml:id="d22fn1">Not printed. It authorized
                        Ambassador Muccio to convey to the Government of the Republic of Korea the
                        text of the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of April 3
                        (895B.13/4–150).</note> Called on President 11 a. m. giving him <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> text Deptel 317 March 31<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d22fn2">See footnote 2 to telegram 432, April 1, from Seoul, <ref
                            target="#pg_39">p. 39</ref>.</note> plus additional paragraph suggested
                        <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 432, April 1.</p>
                <pb facs="0065" n="45" xml:id="pg_45"/>
                <p>President read aloud, then commented much concern. I expressed belief that with
                    President’s earnest backing, following recommendations Economic Stabilization
                    Committee possible establish stabilized financial condition near future, if
                    current delaying tactics overcome. Cited example delaying tactics, specifically
                    recent changing foreign exchange regulations after presidential acceptance
                    committee’s program.</p>
                <p>I said developments anti-democratic character cause considerable concern, citing
                    retention authoritarian Education Minister, constant improper police arrests,
                    use torture threats by high officials against <gloss target="#t_NA1">NA</gloss>.
                    I said would be impossible explain election postponement by government.</p>
                <p>President finally asked what he could do satisfy Secretary and Hoffman. I
                    replied, (1) cause passage laws, budget and taxes, and (2) hold elections before
                    end May.<note n="3" xml:id="d22fn3">For a report on subsequent developments, see
                        despatch no. 435, April 28, from Seoul, <ref target="#pg_52">p.
                        52</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
